1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:47,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:00:55,326 --> 00:01:01,124
JULY 2014

4
00:01:01,207 --> 00:01:03,418
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

5
00:01:03,501 --> 00:01:05,211
5:09 A.M.

6
00:01:13,219 --> 00:01:15,847
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

7
00:01:18,349 --> 00:01:23,938
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

8
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:28,484
Hello.

9
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:34,115
Hui-seo, you think can you walk?

10
00:01:35,325 --> 00:01:36,200
Yeah.

11
00:01:41,748 --> 00:01:42,999
Hui-seo, get on my back.

12
00:01:44,542 --> 00:01:46,711
Hui-seo, try to stand. You can do it.

13
00:01:46,794 --> 00:01:49,255
-Don't trouble your brother.
-Ma'am, it's fine.

14
00:01:51,966 --> 00:01:53,134
Hui-seo.

15
00:01:53,218 --> 00:01:55,678
Okay. One, two, three.

16
00:02:02,769 --> 00:02:04,145
Are you feeling okay?

17
00:02:12,028 --> 00:02:12,946
Sorry.

18
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:17,992
You okay?

19
00:02:27,085 --> 00:02:33,800
STILL SHINING

20
00:02:44,894 --> 00:02:46,020
You think you can you walk?

21
00:02:47,105 --> 00:02:48,064
Goodness.

22
00:02:48,731 --> 00:02:50,483
Grandma, could you move back a bit?

23
00:02:51,067 --> 00:02:52,026
I'll come down.

24
00:02:52,944 --> 00:02:55,071
Come over here. He said he can manage.

25
00:03:01,077 --> 00:03:03,121
-I'm pretty good, right?
-Yes, well done.

26
00:03:03,204 --> 00:03:05,873
I told you I'm all better now.
You don't have to worry about me.

27
00:03:05,957 --> 00:03:07,667
I'm very proud of you.

28
00:03:08,793 --> 00:03:10,211
Goodness. Hi, Tae-seo.

29
00:03:10,962 --> 00:03:13,089
-It's good to see you.
-Have you been well?

30
00:03:13,172 --> 00:03:15,967
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR GRADUATION

31
00:03:19,554 --> 00:03:20,513
My medical report?

32
00:03:21,139 --> 00:03:23,516
You might not be ready for school
when classes start,

33
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,309
so I'll submit it for you.

34
00:03:26,102 --> 00:03:28,104
I'm going to school, even if I'm hurt.

35
00:03:28,187 --> 00:03:30,148
You came all the way here for my sake.

36
00:03:30,231 --> 00:03:32,150
I'm not a kid. I can manage just fine.

37
00:03:33,234 --> 00:03:35,194
I can just take Bus 19 at the bus stop.

38
00:03:40,742 --> 00:03:42,243
Hey, the bus stop!

39
00:03:42,327 --> 00:03:43,244
Grandpa!

40
00:03:43,911 --> 00:03:45,538
Stop! Tae-seo's going to school.

41
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:52,045
Right, your grandfather was worried
that Hui-seo would have trouble walking.

42
00:03:52,128 --> 00:03:55,131
He can walk fine on crutches,
and I'll go with him to and from school.

43
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:58,092
I saw him playing soccer last summer.

44
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,345
I also talked with your father.

45
00:04:01,387 --> 00:04:03,681
My parents both worked,

46
00:04:03,765 --> 00:04:05,683
so Hui-seo always came here
during vacation.

47
00:04:06,392 --> 00:04:08,394
Right. Well, you hang in there too.

48
00:04:09,312 --> 00:04:12,065
The local elementary school
closed last year,

49
00:04:12,148 --> 00:04:14,192
and there's been talk
about us closing too.

50
00:04:15,193 --> 00:04:17,195
But Hui-seo should be able to graduate.

51
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:19,197
We don't get any transfers.

52
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,990
You're the first in five years.

53
00:04:21,074 --> 00:04:22,075
I see.

54
00:04:22,158 --> 00:04:23,076
So…

55
00:04:23,659 --> 00:04:25,578
Did my documents and transcripts arrive?

56
00:04:26,287 --> 00:04:27,330
I'm looking for them now.

57
00:04:27,872 --> 00:04:29,040
Yes, they're all here.

58
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:32,293
And I see
this is your second transfer this year.

59
00:04:33,336 --> 00:04:35,546
Why didn't you just come straight here?

60
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:38,132
My aunt said
I had to go to college in Seoul.

61
00:04:38,216 --> 00:04:39,717
Living in Seoul won't guarantee that.

62
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:41,928
You didn't cause trouble there, right?

63
00:04:42,011 --> 00:04:43,304
No, of course not.

64
00:04:43,388 --> 00:04:45,723
Hui-seo found it hard adjusting to Seoul.

65
00:04:45,807 --> 00:04:46,808
Why?

66
00:04:47,809 --> 00:04:49,560
He was being bullied.

67
00:04:49,644 --> 00:04:53,147
God, those awful punks.
Doing that to someone who's hurt…

68
00:04:53,231 --> 00:04:56,484
I'll keep an eye on him,
so don't worry too much.

69
00:04:56,567 --> 00:05:01,406
With us, all the kids aiming for college
have transferred to schools in the city.

70
00:05:01,489 --> 00:05:04,325
The rest who remain here
help out with their family businesses,

71
00:05:04,409 --> 00:05:06,077
so they have no pressure to study.

72
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:10,164
Anyway, let's make sure
you get your high school diploma here.

73
00:05:11,499 --> 00:05:12,708
And no need to buy a uniform.

74
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:16,379
We have some
that our graduates handed down.

75
00:05:16,462 --> 00:05:18,005
You should grab Hui-seo's as well.

76
00:05:18,089 --> 00:05:19,006
Okay.

77
00:05:19,715 --> 00:05:23,219
This one's for winter. The summer ones
are in front of the library upstairs.

78
00:05:23,761 --> 00:05:25,513
They're usually inside the library,

79
00:05:25,596 --> 00:05:26,931
but there's a kid named Mo Eun-a.

80
00:05:27,014 --> 00:05:29,642
She's doing independent study there,
so we moved them outside.

81
00:05:30,226 --> 00:05:31,978
She's the transfer from five years ago.

82
00:05:42,905 --> 00:05:47,869
LIBRARY

83
00:06:17,732 --> 00:06:19,192
UNIFORM DONATION BOX (SUMMER)

84
00:06:27,074 --> 00:06:28,910
Hey, what on earth is this?

85
00:06:30,494 --> 00:06:32,205
It got crumpled in my bag.

86
00:06:32,288 --> 00:06:34,332
They're my mock exam scores
from March and June.

87
00:06:34,415 --> 00:06:36,417
I thought you may need them
for college counseling.

88
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,961
No, the crumpling isn't the issue.
Look at this.

89
00:06:39,629 --> 00:06:41,964
Top-ranked student multiple times,
all 99s for grades,

90
00:06:42,048 --> 00:06:44,634
and in the highest percentile
in all major subjects.

91
00:06:44,717 --> 00:06:48,054
Geez, with these grades,
you can take your pick of med schools!

92
00:06:48,137 --> 00:06:51,599
You should have this framed,
not shoved into your bag.

93
00:06:52,934 --> 00:06:54,018
Gosh, you're…

94
00:06:58,272 --> 00:06:59,440
Gosh…

95
00:08:26,569 --> 00:08:28,279
Your desk didn't arrive.

96
00:08:28,362 --> 00:08:30,364
I told them a while ago.

97
00:08:31,657 --> 00:08:33,451
Goodness, what a mess.

98
00:08:37,413 --> 00:08:41,250
YEON CHANG-SIK

99
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:47,006
Tae-seo's here.

100
00:08:48,466 --> 00:08:50,509
Gosh, good job finding your way here!

101
00:08:51,427 --> 00:08:52,970
But we have a problem.

102
00:08:53,054 --> 00:08:54,597
Your desk didn't arrive.

103
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:55,848
I already told him.

104
00:08:56,849 --> 00:08:59,727
We should've made sure it arrived today.

105
00:09:00,811 --> 00:09:02,104
It's okay, Grandma.

106
00:09:02,688 --> 00:09:05,316
Right, I'll make sure
to tell them tomorrow.

107
00:09:05,399 --> 00:09:07,485
Why did you have to throw out
his father's desk?

108
00:09:09,528 --> 00:09:11,322
Why are you talking about his father?

109
00:09:11,405 --> 00:09:14,742
I'm just saying you could've thrown it out
after the new one came.

110
00:10:19,765 --> 00:10:21,475
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
CLASS 3-1

111
00:10:56,886 --> 00:11:00,055
The lights didn't even come on
since it's summer break, so I made a fuss.

112
00:11:00,848 --> 00:11:03,684
I heard they make you do independent study
until 10:00 p.m. in Seoul,

113
00:11:03,768 --> 00:11:06,145
so the least they could do
is help me study here.

114
00:11:06,896 --> 00:11:10,316
So now, just the library has power,
and I can use the fans.

115
00:11:12,777 --> 00:11:13,861
Turn that one on.

116
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:21,202
Which bus did you take?

117
00:11:22,745 --> 00:11:23,787
The 6:12 a.m. bus.

118
00:11:24,663 --> 00:11:25,581
That's the first one.

119
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,586
Sit wherever you like.

120
00:11:49,146 --> 00:11:50,981
You can switch into study mode right away?

121
00:11:53,442 --> 00:11:55,736
I need to warm up first. Don't mind me.

122
00:12:09,959 --> 00:12:11,001
Let me say one thing.

123
00:12:11,585 --> 00:12:12,795
Just this. I promise.

124
00:12:14,338 --> 00:12:15,256
Go on.

125
00:12:17,091 --> 00:12:20,052
I suddenly have time
to spend on myself now.

126
00:12:21,095 --> 00:12:22,596
I was taking care of my dad…

127
00:12:25,307 --> 00:12:26,850
But I won't get into that.

128
00:12:27,893 --> 00:12:29,937
I just didn't want to waste this time,

129
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,939
so I decided to study.

130
00:12:32,022 --> 00:12:35,067
I wasn't planning on going to college,
but I think I will.

131
00:12:35,776 --> 00:12:37,319
I don't know what I want to become,

132
00:12:37,403 --> 00:12:38,946
but I'll figure it out as I go.

133
00:12:39,863 --> 00:12:42,449
I know it won't change much,
but I'm giving it a go.

134
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:45,327
What I mean is,
I was never big on studying.

135
00:12:49,164 --> 00:12:50,332
Just saying.

136
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,042
Right.

137
00:12:52,668 --> 00:12:54,211
So my point was,

138
00:12:54,295 --> 00:12:56,005
that's why I need to warm up.

139
00:12:56,672 --> 00:12:57,923
I move around, so bear with me.

140
00:12:58,007 --> 00:12:59,592
Okay, do as you please.

141
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:07,224
The Wi-Fi password.

142
00:13:08,225 --> 00:13:09,977
I downloaded some online lectures,

143
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:12,229
so I'll lend you my USB if you need them.

144
00:13:12,938 --> 00:13:13,856
I'm fine.

145
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,989
Blue is for seniors, green for juniors,
and sophomores are…

146
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,824
Maybe yellow?

147
00:13:25,951 --> 00:13:27,328
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
MO EUN-A

148
00:13:34,168 --> 00:13:36,587
You're Yeon Tae-seo.
Hui-seo's older brother.

149
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:38,130
We call your place "Hui-seo's."

150
00:14:03,197 --> 00:14:04,114
Sorry.

151
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:27,406
The men's room is to the right.

152
00:15:48,761 --> 00:15:50,137
What about lunch?

153
00:15:55,601 --> 00:15:57,102
That's definitely gone bad.

154
00:16:06,945 --> 00:16:08,864
TEACHERS' LOUNGE

155
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,033
I'll restock the ramyeon I eat.

156
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:15,120
Vacation's almost over anyway.
Two a day will last us just fine.

157
00:16:15,204 --> 00:16:18,123
I bought plenty in case anyone dropped by.

158
00:16:33,722 --> 00:16:34,723
For you and Hui-seo.

159
00:16:34,807 --> 00:16:37,434
Gym uniforms are valuable,
so upperclassmen never pass them on.

160
00:16:37,518 --> 00:16:39,061
They wear them forever.

161
00:16:39,144 --> 00:16:42,564
These are magic shorts.
They fit in middle school and as an adult.

162
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,983
They always fit perfectly.

163
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:47,194
It's amazing. They're so comfy too. Look!

164
00:16:47,277 --> 00:16:49,947
Hey! Come on, don't!

165
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:51,115
You startled me.

166
00:16:52,574 --> 00:16:53,909
I'm just saying I'm wearing them.

167
00:16:55,119 --> 00:16:56,995
Thanks for these.

168
00:17:02,543 --> 00:17:04,378
Your grandma's homemade kimchi.

169
00:17:05,587 --> 00:17:07,047
This is really special.

170
00:17:09,675 --> 00:17:11,135
When we were trading items,

171
00:17:11,218 --> 00:17:14,555
we gave Hui-seo his soccer cleats
for your sesame oil and perilla oil.

172
00:17:14,638 --> 00:17:18,016
She thanked me every time she saw me
and then gave me a tub of kimchi.

173
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:20,894
This kimchi is what my dad and I
treasure the most.

174
00:17:20,978 --> 00:17:22,187
Hui-seo's soccer cleats?

175
00:17:22,271 --> 00:17:23,897
Yeah, last fall.

176
00:17:23,981 --> 00:17:25,858
You were the one who bought them?

177
00:17:25,941 --> 00:17:27,693
I told you it was a trade.

178
00:17:27,776 --> 00:17:30,737
Your grandma would never know
what to get Hui-seo whenever he visited.

179
00:17:30,821 --> 00:17:34,950
The shoe bag and Park Ji-sung's jersey.
They were all my idea.

180
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:37,494
She asks me for help every year.
Just for Hui-seo's gifts.

181
00:17:38,453 --> 00:17:39,830
She said you didn't want any.

182
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:44,293
Eat up.

183
00:17:55,888 --> 00:17:57,514
Time to catch the bus.

184
00:17:58,974 --> 00:18:01,685
If you miss this one,
the next one comes in an hour and a half.

185
00:18:06,481 --> 00:18:07,566
Are you coming tomorrow?

186
00:18:07,649 --> 00:18:09,693
I'm in charge of opening
and closing the library.

187
00:18:09,776 --> 00:18:11,486
If you take the 6:50 bus, I'll be here--

188
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:12,696
Don't worry about me.

189
00:18:15,616 --> 00:18:18,535
I don't know if I'm coming tomorrow yet,
so don't worry about me.

190
00:18:20,287 --> 00:18:21,205
Fine.

191
00:18:28,587 --> 00:18:29,504
Aren't you going?

192
00:18:30,255 --> 00:18:31,173
I came on my bike.

193
00:18:34,676 --> 00:18:36,595
I waited so I could tell you the bus time.

194
00:18:50,234 --> 00:18:51,777
Run! You'll miss the bus.

195
00:18:52,986 --> 00:18:54,821
You can see fireflies even in the fall!

196
00:19:08,627 --> 00:19:11,213
Hui-seo, I'm cold. Let's go home.

197
00:19:12,089 --> 00:19:13,632
Yeon Hui-seo, listen to your mother.

198
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,677
We're going on ahead.

199
00:19:18,929 --> 00:19:22,391
Come on!
That bug's not around in the fall.

200
00:19:23,475 --> 00:19:25,560
They all die after the summer.

201
00:19:25,644 --> 00:19:26,478
Hurry up.

202
00:19:27,396 --> 00:19:28,855
Hey, it's a firefly!

203
00:19:30,148 --> 00:19:31,525
Where?

204
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:34,069
Hey, it really is a firefly!

205
00:19:35,862 --> 00:19:38,573
There's so many! Grab them!

206
00:19:38,657 --> 00:19:39,616
Dad!

207
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:43,370
-Where's Hui-seo? Isn't he coming?
-I don't know. He's catching fireflies.

208
00:19:43,996 --> 00:19:46,164
We grew up eating fireflies
back in the day.

209
00:19:46,248 --> 00:19:47,708
-Seriously?
-You're lying.

210
00:19:47,791 --> 00:19:50,377
-You ate them?
-Eating a firefly makes you electric.

211
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:51,378
Don't be silly.

212
00:19:51,461 --> 00:19:53,255
-Dad is so unfunny.
-Yeah.

213
00:20:24,870 --> 00:20:26,913
Does your grandpa not know
how big you are now?

214
00:20:26,997 --> 00:20:28,874
He really is clueless.

215
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:31,710
It's okay.

216
00:20:31,793 --> 00:20:32,961
It's nice and sturdy.

217
00:20:33,045 --> 00:20:35,172
Tae-seo can study anywhere.

218
00:20:35,255 --> 00:20:36,965
As long as he can sit, it's fine.

219
00:20:37,049 --> 00:20:38,717
Did you walk a bit today?

220
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,260
Of course.

221
00:20:40,344 --> 00:20:44,181
I'm fine. Look. I'll be flying around
once the cast comes off.

222
00:20:44,264 --> 00:20:45,223
Just you wait and see.

223
00:20:45,807 --> 00:20:49,019
What should I pack for your lunch
to take to school tomorrow?

224
00:20:49,102 --> 00:20:51,772
He's not going to school, Grandma.
He has a desk now.

225
00:20:53,106 --> 00:20:55,359
I want bibim-guksu for lunch tomorrow.

226
00:20:55,442 --> 00:20:57,319
-Sounds great.
-I'm craving it.

227
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,511
This is a bit hard to open.

228
00:21:25,639 --> 00:21:28,600
-Did you see me last Chuseok?
-I saw you every year.

229
00:21:28,683 --> 00:21:31,353
You stopped coming
in the summer after eighth grade.

230
00:21:32,562 --> 00:21:35,690
Even during Chuseok, you only stayed
briefly because you had to study.

231
00:21:37,109 --> 00:21:39,528
What happened? You acted like
you weren't coming today.

232
00:21:39,611 --> 00:21:41,196
I have to study.

233
00:21:43,573 --> 00:21:45,158
Since when have you known me?

234
00:21:45,909 --> 00:21:49,287
I moved here five years ago, so since
your last summer visit five years ago.

235
00:21:50,747 --> 00:21:52,374
Why the sudden interest?

236
00:21:54,292 --> 00:21:56,711
So you were nice to me
because you knew me.

237
00:21:58,046 --> 00:21:59,840
I'm just saying that I get it now.

238
00:22:03,677 --> 00:22:06,555
If you pick a spot and hide the key,
I'll open up if I arrive early.

239
00:22:07,681 --> 00:22:08,640
No.

240
00:22:08,723 --> 00:22:11,977
The school entrusted it to me,
so I need to open and close up.

241
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:14,312
You can show up whenever and just study.

242
00:22:14,396 --> 00:22:16,022
The key is my responsibility.

243
00:22:19,234 --> 00:22:20,360
What?

244
00:22:21,153 --> 00:22:22,404
I didn't say anything.

245
00:22:26,158 --> 00:22:28,952
You don't have to know someone
to be nice to them.

246
00:22:29,035 --> 00:22:30,412
We're both just country kids here.

247
00:22:35,917 --> 00:22:37,961
It's going to be another hot day today.

248
00:23:08,408 --> 00:23:09,492
Do you want to use this?

249
00:23:10,869 --> 00:23:12,579
Yeah, thanks.

250
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,354
-What?
-What?

251
00:23:39,147 --> 00:23:40,273
It looks good on you.

252
00:23:49,282 --> 00:23:51,076
Where's your bike?

253
00:23:51,159 --> 00:23:52,285
I took the bus today.

254
00:23:52,869 --> 00:23:54,120
I brought my bike today.

255
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:58,833
Well, I just thought I'd ride with you
and get a little exercise.

256
00:24:00,835 --> 00:24:01,920
Then, go exercise.

257
00:24:37,706 --> 00:24:38,790
I'm getting off.

258
00:24:56,099 --> 00:24:59,311
Sir, quickly! Hurry!

259
00:25:49,903 --> 00:25:51,196
I'm not getting on.

260
00:25:51,279 --> 00:25:52,947
Don't you dare try to give me a ride.

261
00:26:02,123 --> 00:26:03,333
Are you serious?

262
00:27:09,566 --> 00:27:10,483
What's wrong?

263
00:27:32,255 --> 00:27:34,674
-The weather's nice.
-Yeah.

264
00:27:38,094 --> 00:27:39,220
Are you getting tired?

265
00:27:39,804 --> 00:27:40,638
No.

266
00:27:41,723 --> 00:27:42,557
Are you hot?

267
00:27:43,266 --> 00:27:44,267
No.

268
00:27:45,393 --> 00:27:46,644
Do you want to eat ice cream?

269
00:27:46,728 --> 00:27:47,562
No.

270
00:27:49,105 --> 00:27:49,939
Yeah.

271
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:19,969
Try throwing it farther.

272
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:28,895
Hey, the bus is coming.

273
00:28:30,313 --> 00:28:31,731
Your bag!

274
00:28:32,315 --> 00:28:33,566
Your bag.

275
00:28:48,456 --> 00:28:52,794
MO EUN-A

276
00:28:53,962 --> 00:28:55,088
YEON TAE-SEO

277
00:29:11,271 --> 00:29:12,689
It's really hot.

278
00:29:36,754 --> 00:29:37,839
Hello.

279
00:30:00,445 --> 00:30:02,947
-Husik.
-Husik?

280
00:30:06,117 --> 00:30:07,577
That name doesn't feel right.

281
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:09,245
Chal-oksusu.

282
00:30:09,329 --> 00:30:12,040
-Chal-oksoso.
-Oksusu.

283
00:30:12,123 --> 00:30:14,375
-Oksosu?
-Susu.

284
00:30:14,459 --> 00:30:16,586
-Susu.
-Oksusu.

285
00:30:16,669 --> 00:30:18,588
Oksusu.

286
00:30:33,102 --> 00:30:35,146
Thanks for making dinner.

287
00:30:35,229 --> 00:30:36,648
Sure thing. Eat up.

288
00:30:38,149 --> 00:30:39,442
Did So-hyeon leave?

289
00:30:40,777 --> 00:30:43,655
Yeah, she went to Seoul
with the guests from Hawaii.

290
00:30:47,158 --> 00:30:48,868
You were drinking, weren't you?

291
00:30:50,244 --> 00:30:51,663
That's why I feel great.

292
00:30:53,206 --> 00:30:55,375
And then you'll feel worse tomorrow.

293
00:30:56,209 --> 00:30:58,419
No, I'll be fine.
You just focus on studying.

294
00:31:00,338 --> 00:31:02,799
Exactly. That's what
dads are supposed to do.

295
00:31:02,882 --> 00:31:04,801
Tell their children
to just study all the time.

296
00:31:04,884 --> 00:31:07,428
It feels great
that I finally get to hear that now.

297
00:31:08,638 --> 00:31:10,890
"What's the point of all that?
Just take it easy."

298
00:31:10,974 --> 00:31:12,433
That's what you always used to say.

299
00:31:14,477 --> 00:31:16,104
Just live freely.

300
00:31:16,187 --> 00:31:20,400
Try living in different countries
and search for what you want to do.

301
00:31:21,025 --> 00:31:22,360
As if you're on a journey.

302
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:29,534
Dad.

303
00:31:29,617 --> 00:31:33,496
I've been watching this kid who's been
through a lot but is pushing forward.

304
00:31:34,455 --> 00:31:35,707
It's really moving.

305
00:31:36,416 --> 00:31:38,126
-Someone your age?
-Yeah.

306
00:31:38,918 --> 00:31:41,879
-What a great kid.
-You're great too.

307
00:31:41,963 --> 00:31:43,047
You got all better for me.

308
00:31:45,299 --> 00:31:46,217
All right,

309
00:31:46,300 --> 00:31:47,969
I'll become an even greater dad.

310
00:31:49,929 --> 00:31:51,055
Enough.

311
00:31:55,601 --> 00:31:56,519
All right, I'll stop.

312
00:31:57,770 --> 00:31:59,022
I need to be a great dad.

313
00:32:36,017 --> 00:32:36,851
Mom…

314
00:32:41,439 --> 00:32:42,482
Mom.

315
00:33:05,505 --> 00:33:07,006
Any reservations today?

316
00:33:08,966 --> 00:33:09,801
No.

317
00:33:12,178 --> 00:33:13,846
I guess no energy either.

318
00:33:13,930 --> 00:33:18,184
Your stomach's probably empty,
so take this with the stomach medicine.

319
00:33:19,811 --> 00:33:22,939
I'm just feeling a little weak
because I threw up this morning.

320
00:33:27,235 --> 00:33:29,278
Go to school. Go study.

321
00:33:32,031 --> 00:33:34,659
Just give me five minutes, Dad.
Take the medicine.

322
00:33:34,742 --> 00:33:35,660
Okay?

323
00:33:51,968 --> 00:33:53,136
Yeon Tae-seo!

324
00:34:05,982 --> 00:34:07,066
Here.

325
00:34:07,775 --> 00:34:10,653
-Aren't you coming to school?
-I will. Wait for me.

326
00:34:30,089 --> 00:34:32,675
Dad? Dad!

327
00:34:33,885 --> 00:34:35,052
Dad?

328
00:34:38,723 --> 00:34:39,807
Dad!

329
00:36:01,097 --> 00:36:02,265
Nothing bad happened.

330
00:36:02,348 --> 00:36:04,183
I just freaked out for no reason.

331
00:36:05,685 --> 00:36:06,686
I can't hear you.

332
00:36:08,437 --> 00:36:09,814
Sometimes I can't hear your voice.

333
00:36:09,897 --> 00:36:11,941
Tell me what you just said.

334
00:36:14,443 --> 00:36:17,571
I was acting stupid,
but now, I feel calmer after seeing you.

335
00:36:17,655 --> 00:36:20,658
Seeing you makes me feel at ease.

336
00:37:03,576 --> 00:37:06,037
So-hyeon, what time are you coming today?

337
00:37:15,212 --> 00:37:16,505
I won't be coming today.

338
00:37:24,722 --> 00:37:25,598
Look at me.

339
00:37:28,768 --> 00:37:29,685
Look.

340
00:37:29,769 --> 00:37:31,187
You said it helps.

341
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,534
I know it helps.

342
00:37:46,118 --> 00:37:47,828
But I need to go home right now.

343
00:37:48,621 --> 00:37:50,873
I'll only get in the way
of your studying like this.

344
00:37:50,956 --> 00:37:51,999
It's not good for you.

345
00:37:56,045 --> 00:37:57,338
No, don't.

346
00:38:05,179 --> 00:38:06,680
Go back to studying.

347
00:38:45,219 --> 00:38:47,388
-Tae-seo! Goodness.
-Grandma.

348
00:38:47,471 --> 00:38:51,308
I came here to buy some mosquito coils.
Let's go home together.

349
00:38:51,392 --> 00:38:55,938
Goodness, who's this handsome young man?

350
00:38:56,021 --> 00:38:56,981
Hello.

351
00:38:58,357 --> 00:39:00,818
-Come eat with us. Come, come.
-All right.

352
00:39:00,901 --> 00:39:01,819
I'll carry that.

353
00:39:02,778 --> 00:39:04,363
Go say hello to everyone.

354
00:39:24,925 --> 00:39:26,552
LIBRARY

355
00:40:15,809 --> 00:40:16,894
Name tags?

356
00:40:20,481 --> 00:40:22,149
IM A-SOL
IM JI-SOL

357
00:40:28,239 --> 00:40:29,448
What are these?

358
00:40:37,915 --> 00:40:41,544
I guess it's true that kids in Seoul
say they like someone by giving name tags.

359
00:40:41,627 --> 00:40:44,421
When did they put those in there?
I had no idea.

360
00:40:44,505 --> 00:40:49,051
Im Ji-sol, Kim Eun-su, Im A-sol.
A lot of girls with the last name "Im."

361
00:40:50,803 --> 00:40:51,720
I have no idea.

362
00:40:52,388 --> 00:40:53,305
No idea about what?

363
00:40:55,015 --> 00:40:56,016
Who's the prettiest?

364
00:40:57,268 --> 00:40:58,310
I don't know.

365
00:40:58,978 --> 00:41:02,189
I know who Im Ji-sol is,
but Hyeong-seok's the one who liked her.

366
00:41:02,273 --> 00:41:03,691
So you do know.

367
00:41:03,774 --> 00:41:06,527
Well, she was pretty famous.
She did well in school.

368
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:07,528
So?

369
00:41:09,029 --> 00:41:09,863
I have no idea.

370
00:41:13,492 --> 00:41:15,661
-This is bad.
-What is?

371
00:41:16,412 --> 00:41:19,248
It's stuck in my head.

372
00:41:19,331 --> 00:41:20,916
I memorized their names.

373
00:41:22,126 --> 00:41:23,586
It's not like that.

374
00:41:23,669 --> 00:41:25,462
I really had no idea
they put those in there.

375
00:41:25,546 --> 00:41:26,714
How could you not know?

376
00:41:30,175 --> 00:41:31,468
When you're always tense,

377
00:41:32,136 --> 00:41:34,847
you only see and hear
what's right in front of you.

378
00:41:37,933 --> 00:41:39,435
Are you still tense right now?

379
00:41:42,563 --> 00:41:45,065
Just explain what happened yesterday.
I was really worried.

380
00:41:50,279 --> 00:41:52,990
I told you before
that I was taking care of my dad.

381
00:41:54,533 --> 00:41:56,243
He had severe depression.

382
00:41:56,994 --> 00:41:58,329
He even attempted suicide.

383
00:42:02,041 --> 00:42:05,210
When? Did you see it happen?

384
00:42:05,294 --> 00:42:06,670
I only saw him being taken away.

385
00:42:07,338 --> 00:42:09,715
He got divorced and left his job.

386
00:42:09,798 --> 00:42:12,134
We came nearby here on a trip.

387
00:42:12,217 --> 00:42:15,179
He fell in love with the marshes,
and we moved in five years ago.

388
00:42:15,888 --> 00:42:17,097
It happened that year.

389
00:42:18,015 --> 00:42:20,934
Ever since then,
I get really anxious when he's by himself.

390
00:42:22,645 --> 00:42:24,938
But he got a new job
just before summer break

391
00:42:25,022 --> 00:42:26,732
and also started seeing someone.

392
00:42:26,815 --> 00:42:28,651
If you ask me,
dating made a big difference.

393
00:42:28,734 --> 00:42:31,945
My dad told me to stop hovering around him
and go do what I want.

394
00:42:32,529 --> 00:42:34,865
Before that,
I hadn't even considered college.

395
00:42:34,948 --> 00:42:36,825
I was going to stay and help him out.

396
00:42:37,785 --> 00:42:38,911
So for the first time ever,

397
00:42:38,994 --> 00:42:42,289
I considered a different future
and started studying on my own.

398
00:42:43,374 --> 00:42:45,167
And then, Yeon Tae-seo appeared.

399
00:42:46,085 --> 00:42:47,294
The one Im A-sol likes.

400
00:42:49,797 --> 00:42:51,006
I'll stop. Sorry.

401
00:42:52,508 --> 00:42:53,634
Cut it out.

402
00:42:56,553 --> 00:43:00,891
Yesterday's situation happened
because my dad had changed, but I hadn't.

403
00:43:00,974 --> 00:43:02,935
My dad told me

404
00:43:03,852 --> 00:43:06,105
he thought he'd live with anxiety forever,

405
00:43:06,855 --> 00:43:09,650
but once he saw how trivial it really was,
the anxiety vanished.

406
00:43:11,193 --> 00:43:13,654
And that's exactly
what I experienced yesterday.

407
00:43:14,279 --> 00:43:16,240
I went home, and nothing had happened.

408
00:43:27,084 --> 00:43:29,211
I bet you're not considering
any local universities.

409
00:43:29,837 --> 00:43:31,463
And I'd never get into one in Seoul.

410
00:43:31,547 --> 00:43:32,548
We'll end up apart.

411
00:43:33,298 --> 00:43:35,551
-You're going to Seoul, right?
-Yeah.

412
00:43:36,301 --> 00:43:38,846
My grandparents and Hui-seo
are precious to me,

413
00:43:38,929 --> 00:43:40,639
so I want to help them from a distance.

414
00:43:41,432 --> 00:43:43,726
When I'm too close, I burn out easily.

415
00:43:47,187 --> 00:43:49,356
They're precious,
so you'll distance yourself…

416
00:43:50,899 --> 00:43:54,361
I never considered distance
when thinking about the future.

417
00:44:16,383 --> 00:44:17,593
It's different, right?

418
00:44:18,177 --> 00:44:20,053
It was still bright
at this hour yesterday.

419
00:44:22,181 --> 00:44:23,432
You'll be going to Seoul.

420
00:44:24,725 --> 00:44:27,394
Where will I be
and what will I be doing next summer?

421
00:44:28,395 --> 00:44:31,899
When I thought about the future
all through summer break,

422
00:44:33,567 --> 00:44:36,028
I'd feel good one moment
and then overwhelmed.

423
00:44:36,111 --> 00:44:38,489
Then, I'd feel excited and then down…

424
00:44:39,615 --> 00:44:41,992
What thoughts made you
feel good and excited?

425
00:44:43,577 --> 00:44:46,455
Working like a cool professional
while wearing an employee badge.

426
00:44:46,538 --> 00:44:47,372
What kind of work?

427
00:44:48,874 --> 00:44:50,459
It keeps changing.

428
00:44:50,542 --> 00:44:51,877
It's a teacher one moment

429
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:55,547
and then something like a therapist
or even a regular office worker.

430
00:44:56,340 --> 00:44:59,426
A place with a lot of employees
and a fancy desk.

431
00:44:59,510 --> 00:45:00,886
I like being around people,

432
00:45:00,969 --> 00:45:03,222
so I'll take the elevator
up to the 30th or 40th floor.

433
00:45:03,305 --> 00:45:04,640
And we'll all pour out for lunch.

434
00:45:05,849 --> 00:45:08,977
That sounds like
it'd be a huge, competitive company.

435
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:12,814
I'm pretty good at English, okay?

436
00:45:13,565 --> 00:45:14,733
And I draw vegetables well.

437
00:45:24,618 --> 00:45:26,495
Yeah, you're pretty good.

438
00:45:28,288 --> 00:45:31,041
I know. I'm not saying
this will get me into art school.

439
00:45:32,459 --> 00:45:34,169
But I'll keep looking.

440
00:45:35,003 --> 00:45:36,755
Whatever I do, I want to give it my all.

441
00:45:36,838 --> 00:45:39,508
My dad keeps telling me
to just take it easy and live freely.

442
00:45:40,050 --> 00:45:41,093
But I don't want to.

443
00:45:41,176 --> 00:45:43,387
I'm going to hustle and give it my all.

444
00:45:48,350 --> 00:45:49,351
You?

445
00:45:49,851 --> 00:45:52,771
Hui-seo would always boast
and say you'd go to med school.

446
00:45:52,854 --> 00:45:54,982
That's what you aim for
if you want to study hard.

447
00:45:57,859 --> 00:46:01,321
I only did it to reassure my parents
who were living paycheck to paycheck.

448
00:46:02,155 --> 00:46:03,615
But now, I just feel restless.

449
00:46:03,699 --> 00:46:05,659
I just want to find a job
and start making money.

450
00:46:07,160 --> 00:46:09,705
I'll think about how to live my life
after that happens.

451
00:46:09,788 --> 00:46:13,292
Is it really possible
to think about it afterwards?

452
00:46:14,626 --> 00:46:16,712
If I focus on doing
what I can do right now,

453
00:46:16,795 --> 00:46:18,380
I'm sure I'll end up somewhere.

454
00:46:20,215 --> 00:46:21,550
You sound like a grown-up.

455
00:46:22,676 --> 00:46:25,512
Yeah, right.
I don't even have an ID card yet.

456
00:46:25,596 --> 00:46:27,472
You'll succeed no matter what you do.

457
00:46:28,140 --> 00:46:30,225
You're different from the rest.

458
00:46:30,309 --> 00:46:31,435
I just seem different.

459
00:46:32,227 --> 00:46:33,145
This was special.

460
00:46:36,064 --> 00:46:37,149
I mean our situation.

461
00:46:37,774 --> 00:46:40,193
It was just the two of us
studying in this huge school.

462
00:46:49,161 --> 00:46:50,370
You like people,

463
00:46:50,454 --> 00:46:52,914
you're good at English,
and you draw vegetables well.

464
00:46:52,998 --> 00:46:55,375
I know there's a job out there
you can give your all to.

465
00:46:57,669 --> 00:46:58,754
It'll work out

466
00:46:59,463 --> 00:47:00,964
in ways we never imagined.

467
00:47:03,258 --> 00:47:06,970
We'll know for sure what that is
once we become adults.

468
00:47:14,269 --> 00:47:16,938
Where we'll be, what we'll do,
and with who…

469
00:47:23,487 --> 00:47:25,822
It feels like we've been
studying together all summer,

470
00:47:25,906 --> 00:47:27,074
but it's barely been a month.

471
00:47:27,157 --> 00:47:29,117
It was really nice studying with you.

472
00:47:29,201 --> 00:47:31,953
I felt more motivated
having someone else with me.

473
00:47:32,037 --> 00:47:33,497
I guess I like you.

474
00:47:44,841 --> 00:47:45,926
I'm all packed.

475
00:49:33,617 --> 00:49:34,868
It's been forever!

476
00:49:35,869 --> 00:49:37,370
I want to go home!

477
00:49:57,641 --> 00:49:58,475
Slow down.

478
00:49:59,059 --> 00:50:01,269
Hey, Kim Ji-min. Don't run!

479
00:50:02,062 --> 00:50:04,314
We don't offer physics
or a second foreign language,

480
00:50:04,397 --> 00:50:05,941
so you can study on your own.

481
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,860
Just spend the day
studying at your own pace.

482
00:50:09,736 --> 00:50:10,987
Thank you, sir.

483
00:50:29,631 --> 00:50:31,675
MO EUN-A

484
00:50:42,352 --> 00:50:43,687
Want to play basketball later?

485
00:50:43,770 --> 00:50:44,896
-What do you say?
-For a bet?

486
00:51:00,203 --> 00:51:06,418
SEPTEMBER

487
00:51:06,501 --> 00:51:07,419
You're walking great.

488
00:51:08,169 --> 00:51:09,379
Your Achilles is fully healed.

489
00:51:12,507 --> 00:51:14,843
Grandpa's waiting outside,
so take your time.

490
00:51:18,889 --> 00:51:20,640
Walking like this without a cast

491
00:51:21,558 --> 00:51:22,767
makes it feel real.

492
00:51:26,938 --> 00:51:28,398
I'm stuck like this for life, right?

493
00:51:30,150 --> 00:51:31,276
I'm scared, Tae-seo.

494
00:51:46,458 --> 00:51:48,126
My right leg's fine, so I can do it all.

495
00:51:48,209 --> 00:51:52,213
The doctor also said
this is nothing to worry about.

496
00:51:52,297 --> 00:51:54,466
-Right, Tae-seo?
-Yeah.

497
00:51:56,176 --> 00:51:59,804
When I'm all grown,
I'll be able to drive tractors and stuff.

498
00:52:13,026 --> 00:52:16,780
I might be able to get rid of
the crutches soon.

499
00:52:16,863 --> 00:52:18,031
When I was walking earlier…

500
00:52:18,114 --> 00:52:21,952
OCTOBER

501
00:52:23,078 --> 00:52:24,955
Ladies and gentlemen.

502
00:52:25,038 --> 00:52:26,665
We will shortly arrive at Cheongnyangni…

503
00:52:26,748 --> 00:52:29,209
We're almost at Seoul.
Let's wait at the door.

504
00:52:33,922 --> 00:52:35,090
Gosh, I'm sorry.

505
00:52:52,482 --> 00:52:54,150
You didn't look back even once.

506
00:52:58,196 --> 00:53:00,031
-Where are you headed?
-Where you're going.

507
00:53:00,615 --> 00:53:03,326
I heard you got excused
to go to a college admissions seminar.

508
00:53:03,410 --> 00:53:05,161
I told them I was going as well.

509
00:53:07,831 --> 00:53:10,125
It feels like I haven't seen you in ages.

510
00:53:11,126 --> 00:53:12,252
I'm taking the subway.

511
00:53:13,461 --> 00:53:14,671
I'm on a tight schedule.

512
00:53:14,754 --> 00:53:16,840
I'm taking the subway too. What line?

513
00:53:16,923 --> 00:53:19,134
-Line 2.
-Gangbyeon Station…

514
00:53:19,217 --> 00:53:21,219
Isn't that close to Children's Grand Park?

515
00:53:21,302 --> 00:53:23,888
I think I went there once with my mom.

516
00:53:23,972 --> 00:53:25,015
All kids do at that age.

517
00:53:27,225 --> 00:53:29,769
But I don't know
if it really happened or if I imagined it.

518
00:53:29,853 --> 00:53:31,855
I'm not here to have fun.

519
00:53:35,984 --> 00:53:37,819
What line are you taking?
Do you know the way?

520
00:53:37,902 --> 00:53:39,237
Busy Yeon Tae-seo.

521
00:53:40,905 --> 00:53:41,823
Get going, then.

522
00:53:56,046 --> 00:53:59,466
2015 HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY
ADMISSIONS INFORMATION SESSION

523
00:54:04,012 --> 00:54:05,513
I'm Yeon Tae-seo.

524
00:54:12,645 --> 00:54:14,105
So-hyeon, it's me.

525
00:54:14,189 --> 00:54:16,232
I'm on the subway right now.

526
00:54:16,316 --> 00:54:19,027
You live near Isu Station, right?

527
00:54:19,110 --> 00:54:20,028
Can I come?

528
00:54:22,947 --> 00:54:23,782
Of course.

529
00:54:23,865 --> 00:54:26,326
But take your time. I'm on my way as well.

530
00:54:26,951 --> 00:54:30,497
Come to Unit 610 at Space Inn
on 17 Isujungang-ro.

531
00:54:55,772 --> 00:54:57,107
-You're early.
-Yeah. Did you eat?

532
00:54:57,190 --> 00:54:58,024
Yeah.

533
00:55:02,320 --> 00:55:03,321
You're here.

534
00:55:05,907 --> 00:55:07,075
Who is he?

535
00:55:07,158 --> 00:55:08,284
Let's go inside.

536
00:55:11,162 --> 00:55:11,996
What's the matter?

537
00:55:12,080 --> 00:55:13,873
You're dating my dad.

538
00:55:17,919 --> 00:55:18,753
Eun-a.

539
00:55:18,837 --> 00:55:21,047
-What in the…
-You've got it wrong.

540
00:55:23,091 --> 00:55:25,635
-You said you liked my dad.
-Yes.

541
00:55:26,219 --> 00:55:28,555
Liking someone doesn't always mean
you can date them.

542
00:55:29,180 --> 00:55:30,223
What kind of crap is that?

543
00:55:32,267 --> 00:55:35,103
Your dad won't date anyone.

544
00:55:36,688 --> 00:55:38,481
He's not interested in me.

545
00:55:45,780 --> 00:55:48,116
HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

546
00:55:54,789 --> 00:55:55,748
You're all done.

547
00:55:55,832 --> 00:55:57,876
The results will be ready in an hour.

548
00:55:57,959 --> 00:55:59,043
You can come out now.

549
00:56:00,628 --> 00:56:06,801
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

550
00:56:10,555 --> 00:56:12,432
Hurry and give it. I have to go back now.

551
00:56:12,515 --> 00:56:14,434
Geez, you heartless punk.

552
00:56:14,934 --> 00:56:17,061
How did our teacher know
you were in Seoul?

553
00:56:17,854 --> 00:56:19,230
He booked a seminar for me.

554
00:56:19,856 --> 00:56:21,524
You're always getting special treatment.

555
00:56:22,650 --> 00:56:24,277
I heard your mock exam score dipped.

556
00:56:24,360 --> 00:56:26,613
-He said this might cheer you up.
-What is it?

557
00:56:34,954 --> 00:56:39,542
FAMILY BACKGROUND SURVEY

558
00:56:42,170 --> 00:56:43,713
PARENTS' DESIRED CAREER PATH FOR CHILD

559
00:56:43,796 --> 00:56:45,465
"Something safe and peaceful

560
00:56:46,549 --> 00:56:49,969
where he can make a living
without struggle."

561
00:56:55,225 --> 00:56:57,268
There's no damage to the eardrum.

562
00:56:57,894 --> 00:57:00,355
It's a temporary impairment
caused by exam stress,

563
00:57:00,438 --> 00:57:01,940
and your hearing may come and go.

564
00:57:02,565 --> 00:57:04,400
It should improve after the CSAT.

565
00:57:05,360 --> 00:57:07,487
When did the symptoms begin?

566
00:57:08,321 --> 00:57:10,990
March 3rd…

567
00:57:11,991 --> 00:57:13,826
That's right after starting
your senior year.

568
00:57:17,997 --> 00:57:19,457
No.

569
00:57:20,333 --> 00:57:21,167
So…

570
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:25,213
It was after Hui-seo's entrance ceremony.

571
00:57:26,673 --> 00:57:29,801
They were going to buy him sneakers,
so Mom and Dad…

572
00:57:35,098 --> 00:57:36,266
They got in Dad's cab…

573
00:57:38,893 --> 00:57:40,728
and the three of them
got into an accident.

574
00:57:46,401 --> 00:57:47,777
My parents passed away,

575
00:57:49,237 --> 00:57:50,488
and Hui-seo's leg…

576
00:57:53,908 --> 00:57:55,201
His leg…

577
00:58:00,415 --> 00:58:01,291
Hui-seo's leg…

578
00:58:41,289 --> 00:58:45,293
TAE-SEO

579
00:58:45,376 --> 00:58:46,794
The safety doors are closing.

580
00:58:46,878 --> 00:58:49,422
-Are you still in Seoul?
-I'm not here to have fun either.

581
00:58:51,424 --> 00:58:54,719
-Where are you?
-It was a big leap for me.

582
00:58:54,802 --> 00:58:56,387
I didn't come here to have fun.

583
00:58:57,013 --> 00:58:58,181
I tried distancing myself.

584
00:58:58,264 --> 00:59:00,433
I worked up the courage for the first time

585
00:59:01,643 --> 00:59:03,478
and tried stepping away from my dad.

586
00:59:04,562 --> 00:59:06,981
I thought, "I might make it
if I follow Yeon Tae-seo."

587
00:59:07,065 --> 00:59:09,525
I was able to come
because I thought I was going with you.

588
00:59:12,612 --> 00:59:13,655
Where are you?

589
00:59:17,325 --> 00:59:18,660
The stop after Isu Station.

590
00:59:19,369 --> 00:59:22,538
-I have to get to Cheongnyangni Station.
-Is it Dongjak Station?

591
00:59:24,874 --> 00:59:25,792
Yeah.

592
00:59:29,170 --> 00:59:30,296
Dongjak Station…

593
01:00:21,639 --> 01:00:22,640
The Hangang River.

594
01:00:23,266 --> 01:00:24,934
It's my first time seeing it.

595
01:00:26,644 --> 01:00:28,229
The Hangang River? Where?

596
01:00:29,605 --> 01:00:31,149
Over there. Look closely.

597
01:00:33,735 --> 01:00:34,819
I can't see anything.

598
01:00:40,867 --> 01:00:43,995
I'm seeing the Hangang River
for the first time with Yeon Tae-seo.

599
01:01:02,054 --> 01:01:03,014
What's your deal?

600
01:01:03,097 --> 01:01:04,724
You're completely different now.

601
01:01:05,641 --> 01:01:07,643
You acted like you'd never see me again.

602
01:01:07,727 --> 01:01:09,645
-Earlier, I was--
-Not just earlier.

603
01:01:09,729 --> 01:01:12,565
Ever since summer break ended,
you ignored me and avoided--

604
01:01:27,205 --> 01:01:28,706
The tension finally wore off.

605
01:01:31,334 --> 01:01:34,212
Today, just suddenly.

606
01:01:35,213 --> 01:01:36,339
I know that feeling.

607
01:01:36,964 --> 01:01:38,424
How it happens all of a sudden.

608
01:01:41,052 --> 01:01:44,806
I've felt sick since yesterday evening,
just thinking about leaving Yeonwoo.

609
01:01:45,598 --> 01:01:48,267
But the second I saw you
on the train earlier,

610
01:01:48,351 --> 01:01:51,187
all that anxiety disappeared suddenly.

611
01:01:53,022 --> 01:01:54,023
It's strange.

612
01:01:54,106 --> 01:01:58,945
I've been studying better because of you,
and my grades have improved a little too.

613
01:01:59,529 --> 01:02:00,822
I also worked up my courage.

614
01:02:03,491 --> 01:02:04,992
I wonder what you are to me.

615
01:02:15,920 --> 01:02:16,838
It's the word

616
01:02:18,047 --> 01:02:20,424
you memorized all summer
while sighing the whole time.

617
01:02:24,220 --> 01:02:25,054
Yeah.

618
01:02:25,680 --> 01:02:26,973
I know.

619
01:02:27,056 --> 01:02:28,850
I know it. Don't tell me.

620
01:02:34,730 --> 01:02:35,648
To make possible.

621
01:02:40,236 --> 01:02:41,404
That's what I am.

622
01:03:04,218 --> 01:03:05,136
We'll have to

623
01:03:06,971 --> 01:03:08,264
be together forever.

624
01:03:29,035 --> 01:03:29,911
Let's do that.

625
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:34,874
Starting now.

626
01:03:54,852 --> 01:03:57,772
STILL SHINING

627
01:04:26,509 --> 01:04:28,511
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
